OP-1 checked evidence discharges the reversed/offset derived-index
bounds this row used to pin on. The surviving obligation is
guard-dependent: append emits `i < m` inside the true branch of
`iteM (ltNat i m …)` under only the concatenated bound `i < m + n` —
the branch guard is not available as evidence at the obligation site,
so the bound is unprovable in place. Guarded evidence-less access is
Slice OP-2's surface (the runtime-checked accessor makes the branch
error-faithful). True differential tests may not rely on `sorry`.
